<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4891040>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 14: Proposed geographic and molecular relationships of four southwestern United States Pseudouroctonus species, P. brysoni, sp. nov. (white icon), P. kremani (red icon), P. santarita (green icon), and P. apacheanus (yellow icon). Top. Close-up of southwestern United States, showing the type localities (icon with ‘+’) of the four species. Bottom. A partial chronogram based on molecular data showing proposed phylogenetic relationships based on evolutionary time indicating estimates for a multilocus species tree (red numbers depict means). Information is from Bryson et al. (2013: fig. 3). Altitude data is that of the type localities (icon with ‘+’)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4891040/files/figure.png" .

